o an area of turbulence and icing which resulted in the pilot\'s inability to regain a safe altitude.','Fish Haven, Idaho',7,1953,1,'winter',0),(1604,'1953-01-15 00:00:00','25 nm off Agrigento, Italy','Military -Royal Air Force','Vickers Valetta Mk1 / Avero Lancaster',26,26,0,'Both aircraft crashed after a midair collision at approximately 1,500 ft.  Weather conditions at the time were a factor with localized thundrestorms, heavy rain and hail. The court of enquiry was of the opinion that no responsibility could be attached to any individual.  Although evidence revealed that the  Malta Flight\rInformation Center were not in possession of full information on the Lancaster\'s sortie, it was not a contributory cause. Nineteen killed aboard the Vickers, 7 aboard the Lancaster.','25 nm off Agrigento, Italy',15,1953,1,'winter',0),(1605,'1953-01-26 00:00:00','Sinnai, Sardinia, Italy','Linee Aeree Italiane','Douglas DC-3',19,19,0,'Crashed 10 miles east of Cagliari in the Sinnai mountains after a wing failed due to overstressing.','Sinnai, Sardinia, Italy',26,1953,1,'winter',0),(1606,'1953-02-02 00:00:00','Off Newfoundland, Canada','Lancashire Aircraft Corporation (Skyways)','Avro 685 York 1',39,39,0,'Last know coordinates 46\' 15\" N, 46\'31\"W, over the North Atlantic. A distress message was received. No trace of the aircraft or its occupants were ever found.','Off Newfoundland, Canada',2,1953,2,'winter',0),(1607,'1953-02-03 00:00:00','Lai Chau, Vietnam','Air Outremer','Douglas C-47B-15-DK',18,18,0,'Destroyed by detonation of a bomb.','Lai Chau, Vietnam',3,1953,2,'winter',0),(1608,'1953-02-07 00:00:00','Bordeaux, France','UTA','Douglas C-54A-5-DC',19,9,0,'Crashed into a grove of small trees and burst into flames while trying to land in heavy fog. Misjudgement by the pilot. Wrong altimeter setting.','Bordeaux, France',7,1953,2,'winter',10),(1609,'1953-02-09 00:00:00','Cairo, Egypt','Military - Egyptian Air Force','Curtiss-Wright C-46',40,29,0,'Crashed into a hill during a s