r the Mediterranean Sea','Military - Egyptian Air Force','Curtiss C-46',16,16,0,'Shot down by the Israeli Air Force.','Over the Mediterranean Sea',28,1956,10,'autumn',0),(1864,'1956-11-05 00:00:00','Blackbushe, England','Britavia','Handley Page HP-1 Hermes',80,7,0,'While attempting to land the aircraft descended below the ILS glideslope and hit a tree. Using the lights of the airport the captain misjudged the height he was flying.','Blackbushe, England',5,1956,11,'autumn',73),(1865,'1956-11-07 00:00:00','Hommelfjell, Norway','Braathens','de Havilland DH-114 Heron 2B',12,2,0,'The aircraft took off, experienced icing, lost altitude and crashed into Hommelfjell Mountain. Unusually heavy icing which the aircraft encountered. Severe downdraft immediately prior to the crash may have been a contributing factor.','Hommelfjell, Norway',7,1956,11,'autumn',10),(1866,'1956-11-15 00:00:00','Puerto Somoza, Nicaragua','Aerovias Guest','Douglas C-54A-10-DC',25,25,0,'An unsuccessful belly landing was attempted on flat terrain following a fire in the fuel system.','Puerto Somoza, Nicaragua',15,1956,11,'autumn',0),(1867,'1956-11-17 00:00:00','El Rucio Mountain, Colombia','Empresa Aviacion del Pacifico','Douglas DC-3',36,36,0,'Hit El Rucio Mountain at 6,200 ft. which was obscured by clouds. Lack of cockpit discipline. Flight on instruments at an excessively low altitude for the route.','El Rucio Mountain, Colombia',17,1956,11,'autumn',0),(1868,'1956-11-24 00:00:00','Paris, France','Linee Aeree Italiane','Douglas DC-6B',35,34,8,'Lost altitude on takeoff and crashed into a house. Failed to climb for reasons unknown. The aircraft\'s slight loss of altitude soon after take off was the main cause of the accident. There is no explanation for this loss of altitude. Orchestra and opera conductor Guido Cantelli, 36, among those killed.','Near Eglisau, Switzerland',24,1956,11,'autumn',1),(1869,'1956-11-24 00:00:00','Paris, France','Linee Aeree Italiane','Douglas DC-6B',35,34,8,'Lost altitude on 