iana',17,1960,3,'spring',0),(2140,'1960-03-19 00:00:00','Cordoba, Colombia','SAMSA','Curtiss C-46',46,25,0,'Forced landing after engine failure. The accident was attributed to an error in judgment by the pilot in deciding to land at an airport which was closed and where no radio aid was available. Contributing factors were intermittent overspeeding of propellers, adverse weather and no communication tower.','Cordoba, Colombia',19,1960,3,'spring',21),(2141,'1960-04-05 00:00:00','Siuna, Nicaragua','Lanica','Curtiss C-46A-40-CU',18,2,0,'Flew into a hill shortly after taking off. Engine failure due to a  fatigue crack at a valve.','Siuna, Nicaragua',5,1960,4,'spring',16),(2142,'1960-04-12 00:00:00','Pelotas, Brazil','Cruzeiro','Douglas DC-3',22,10,0,'While taking off, the plane drifted to the right, overcorrected to the left and struck two other aircraft. Pilot error.  Incorrect use of the brakes and controls while on the ground.','Pelotas, Brazil',12,1960,4,'spring',12),(2143,'1960-04-14 00:00:00','Taipei,Taiwan','Military - Royal Thai Air Force','Douglas DC-4',18,18,0,'Struck Mt Wuzhi located 8 km northeast of the airport.','Taipei,Taiwan',14,1960,4,'spring',0),(2144,'1960-04-18 00:00:00','Stephenville, Newfoundland','Military - U.S. Air Force','Douglas C-124C Globemaster',9,9,0,'Failed to gain altitude on take off and struck a hill.','Stephenville, Newfoundland',18,1960,4,'spring',0),(2145,'1960-04-19 00:00:00','Bogota, Colombia','Lloyd Aereo Colombiano','Curtiss C-46',51,37,0,'Crashed during final approach. The pilot failed to take proper action to counteract the loss of speed and height in the final approach turn. Lack of pilot experience.','Bogota, Colombia',19,1960,4,'spring',14),(2146,'1960-04-20 00:00:00','Hickory, North Carolina','Piedmont Airlines / Private','Fairchild F-27 / Cessna 310',44,4,0,'The aircraft were involved in a midair collision while both were making an approach to land. The pilot of the Cessna, the over-taking aircraft, failed to see and avoid the F-27 during the landing appoach. Four died aboard the Cessna, none aboard the Fairchild.','Hickory, North Carolina',20,1960,4,'spring',40),(2147,'1960-04-22 00:00:00','Bunia, Belgian Congo','Sobelair SA (Belgium)','Douglas C-54B',35,35,0,'Crashed into the slope of Bogoro Peak located about 8 km short of runway.while on approach. Crew error. The decision by the pilot in descending below the minimum ceiling prescribed.','Bunia, Belgian Congo',22,1960,4,'spring',0),(2148,'1960-04-28 00:00:00','Near Calabozo, Venezuela','Linea Aeropostal Venezolana','Douglas DC-3',13,13,0,'The aircraft crashed after an explosion aboard. Detonation of a hand-grenade brought aboard by a Russian immigrant. The explosion occurred after the captain tried to disarm the man.','Near Calabozo, Venezuela',28,1960,4,'spring',0),(2149,'1960-05-15 00:00:00','Jebel Marra, Sudan','Balair','Douglas DC-4-1009',12,12,0,'Crashed into 8,000 ft. Mt. Marra. Navigation error by the crew who were using an astrofix to estimate their position.','Jebel Marra, Sudan',15,1960,5,'spring',0),(2150,'1960-05-18 00:00:00','El Sosneado, Argentina','Transamerican Air Transport','Curtiss C-46',9,9,0,'Crashed due to structural failure after flying into extremely violent turbulence. Insufficient preparation for the flight by the crew. Inadequate arrangements for the secure carriage of the livestock. The pilots failure to familiarize himself with the prevailing weather conditions. Not found until 11/21/61.','El Sosneado, Argentina',18,1960,5,'spring',0),(2151,'1960-05-23 00:00:00','Atlanta, Georgia','Delta Air Lines','Convair CV-880',4,4,0,'The aircraft stalled for reasons undetermined, at an altitude too low to effect recovery.','Atlanta, Georgia',23,1960,5,'spring',0),(2152,'1960-06-10 00:00:00','Nea Tkvarcheli, Georgia','Aeroflot','Ilyushin IL-14P',31,31,0,'The plane crashed in hillside woods while en route. Poor organization and overseeing the preparation of the flight by the crew.','Nea Tkvarcheli, Georgia',10,1960,6,'summer',0),(2153,'1960-06-10 00:00:00','Nea Tkvarcheli, Georgia','Aeroflot','Ilyushin IL-14P',31,31,0,'The plane crashed in hillside woods while en route. Poor organization and overseeing the preparation of the flight by the crew.','Off  Mackay, Qld. Australia',10,1960,6,'summer',0),(2154,'1960-06-10 00:00:00','Off  Mackay, Qld. Australia','Trans Australia Airlines','Fokker F-27 Friendship 100',29,29,0,'The flight crashed into the sea, 7.5 miles from the airport after being in a holding pattern waiting for fog to lift.  Cause could not be determined.','Nea Tkvarcheli, Georgia',10,1960,6,'summer',0),(2155,'1960-06-10 00:00:00','Off  Mackay, Qld. Australia','Trans Australia Airlines','Fokker F-27 Friendship 100',29,29,0,'The flight crashed into the sea, 7.5 miles from the airport after being in a holding pattern waiting for fog to lift.  Cause could not be determined.','Off  Mackay, Qld. Australia',10,1960,6,'summer',0),(2156,'1960-06-14 00:00:00','Mt. Gilbert, Alaska','Pacific Northern Airlines','Lockheed 749A-79-32 Constellation',14,14,0,'The aircraft failed to maintain its intended flight path and  crashed into the face of Mt. Gilbert at 9,646 ft. after taking off from Cordova. The crew\'s failure to use all available  navigational aids in establishing the aircraft\'s position on Amber I Airway thereby allowing the aircraft  to proceed off course over dangerous terrain. A contributing factor to the  accident was the failure of air defense radar, which had been tracking the aircraft, to notify either  ARTCC or the crew that the aircraft was proceeding on a dangerous course.','Mt. Gilbert, Alaska',14,1960,6,'summer',0),(2157,'1960-06-24 00:00:00','Rio de Janeiro, Brazil','REAL','Convair CV-340-62',54,54,0,'Crashed into Guanabara Bay during approach. Cause undetermined.','Rio de Janeiro, Brazil',24,1960,6,'summer',0),(2158,'1960-07-06 00:00:00','Off Barnegat City, New Jersey','Military - U.S. Navy','Goodyear ZPG-3W (airship)',21,18,0,'The airship crashed nose-firs