as killed. A total of nine persons were involved in the hijacking.','Toledo, Ohio',29,1960,10,'autumn',36),(2193,'1960-10-29 00:00:00','Key West, Florida','Cubana de Aviacion','Douglas DC-3',37,1,0,'Ten minutes into the flight the copilot grabbing the air marshall and forcing the pilot at gunpoint to head to Key West. A shooting erupted and the air marshall was killed. A total of nine persons were involved in the hijacking.','Key West, Florida',29,1960,10,'autumn',36),(2194,'1960-10-29 00:00:00','Toledo, Ohio','Arctic Pacific','Curtiss C-46F-1-CU',48,22,0,'Crashed after taking off from Toledo Express Airfield, landing 5,800 ft. beyond the runway threshold. Sixteen members of the California State  Polytechnic College,  San Luis Obispo football team killed. Premature lift-off, partial loss of power in the No.1 engine, overweight aircraft and weather conditions were the cause of the crash.','Toledo, Ohio',29,1960,10,'autumn',26),(2195,'1960-10-29 00:00:00','Toledo, Ohio','Arctic Pacific','Curtiss C-46F-1-CU',48,22,0,'Crashed after taking off from Toledo Express Airfield, landing 5,800 ft. beyond the runway threshold. Sixteen members of the California State  Polytechnic College,  San Luis Obispo football team killed. Premature lift-off, partial loss of power in the No.1 engine, overweight aircraft and weather conditions were the cause of the crash.','Key West, Florida',29,1960,10,'autumn',26),(2196,'1960-11-05 00:00:00','Bhairawa, Nepal','Royal Nepal Airlines','Douglas C-47A',4,4,0,'While in  the initial climb, the plane stalled and crashed in a huge explosion.','Bhairawa, Nepal',5,1960,11,'autumn',0),(2197,'1960-11-07 00:00:00','Near Quito, Ecuador','AREA','Fairchild F-27A',37,37,0,'Crashed into a mountain 20 miles south of the airport while on approoach to Quito-Mariscal Sucre Airport.','Near Quito, Ecuador',7,1960,11,'autumn',0),(2198,'1960-11-23 00:00:00','Manila, Philippines','Philippine Air Lines','Douglas DC-3',33,33,0,'Crashed into Mt. Baco while en route. Navigational error under adverse weather conditions.','Manila, Philippines',23,1960,11,'autumn',0),(2199,'1960-12-04 00:00:00','Chernovo, Russia','Aeroflot','Ilyushin 14M',14,14,0,'The right engine caught fire. The crew initiated an emergency  descent from which the right wing broke off  causing the aircraft to crash.','Chernovo, Russia',4,1960,12,'winter',0),(2200,'1960-12-07 00:00:00','Cachimbo, Brazil','REAL','Curtiss C-46A-60-CK',15,15,0,'The No.2 engine failed while en route. The aircraft lost altitude, crashed in a jungle and burned. Starboard engine failed to feather for reasons unknown.','Cachimbo, Brazil',7,1960,12,'winter',0),(2201,'1960-12-11 00:00:00','San Andres de Giles, Argentina','Military - Argentine Air Force','Avro 691 Lancastrian IV',31,31,0,'The domestic flight cashed and burned in heavy rain, 100 miles from it\'s destination. Pilot error. Flying VFR in adverse weather conditions.','San Andres de Giles, Argentina',11,1960,12,'winter',0),(2202,'1960-12-16 00:00:00','Staten Island / Brooklyn, New York','United Air Lines / Trans World Airlines','MD DC-8-11 / Lockheed  1049 S Const',128,128,6,'A midair collision took place over Staten Island at 5,000 ft. The Connie was cleared to land at La Guardia Airport on Runway 04 when the United DC-8 struck the Connie tearing it apart. The Connie immediately crashed to the ground at Miller Army Air Field on Staten Island. One passenger was sucked out into one of the DC8s jet engines. Other passengers fell from the Connie as the spinning fuselage fell onto Staten Island. The United jet tried to make an emergency landing at La Guardia Airport but could not maintain altitude and crashed into the streets of Brooklyn. Forty-four people on the Constellation and eight-four people on the DC-8 were killed. Three passengers from the DC-8 died shortly after. One young boy, Stephen Baltz survived several days before succumbing to his injuries. Six people were also killed on the ground. The United crew entered a low-altitude holding pattern at 500 miles per hour, twice the speed it should have been going and flew past the clearance limits and airspace allocated to the flight. One of 2 VORs on the DC-8 was not functioning. Although the crew knew this, they failed to report this to the ATC, who probably would have provided extra radar assistance.','Staten Island / Brooklyn, New York',16,1960,12,'winter',0),(2203,'1960-12-17 00:00:00','Munich, West Germany','Military - U.S. Air Force','Convair C-131D (CV-340-79)',20,20,31,'The aircraft lost an engine on takeoff from Munich. Unable to maintain altitude, the aircraft crashed into St. Paul\'s Cathedral church and into a crowded streetcar in the business section of the city, breeching a gas main and starting a fierce fire, Thirty-one people were killed on the ground. A collection of water was found in the fuel tank booster pump. Fuel contamination causing engine failure.','Munich, West Germany',17,1960,12,'winter',0),(2204,'1960-12-22 00:00:00','Cebu City, Philippines','Philippine Air Lines','Douglas DC-3',37,28,0,'Crashed on takeoff. Failure of the No. 1 engine shortly after take-off but after V2. Inappropriate emergency procedures by crew.','Cebu City, Philippines',22,1960,12,'winter',9),(2205,'1960-12-26 00:00:00','Near Ulyanovsk, Russia','Aeroflot','Ilyushin IL-18A',17,17,0,'Loss of control resulted after 40 degrees flaps was selected causing the plane to crash. Icing.','Near Ulyanovsk, Russia',26,1960,12,'winter',0),(2206,'1961-01-02 00:00:00','Ruzyne, Czechoslovakia','Ceskoslovenske Aerolinie','Avia 14',10,10,0,'Unable to gain altitude, the aircraft crashed into power cables during takeoff.','Ruzyne, Czechoslovakia',2,1961,1,'winter',0),(2207,'1961-01-03 00:00:00','Koivulahti, Finland','Finnair','Douglas DC-3',25,25,0,'Crashed into woods while attempting to land. Both pilots tested positive for alcohol.  In addition, the pilot did not have enough sleep the night before and was not considered to be in satisfactory mental and physical condition to undertake the flight.','Koivulahti, Finland',3,1961,1,'winter',0),(2208,'1961-01-19 00:00:00','New York, New York (Idlewild)','Aeronaves de Mexico','McDonnell Douglas DC-8-21',106,4,0,'An aborted takeoff caused the aircraft to crash through the airport barrier fence and burst into flames. The unnecessary discontinuance of the takeoff as a result of actions by the check-pilot who was either not in the pilot\'s seat or reached forward without warning and pulling the throttles back. This action caused power to be decreased on all four engines. Contributing factors were the marginally poor weather, snow on the runway and the possibility of the pitot head heat not being on.','New York, New York (Idlewild)',19,1961,1,'winter',102),(2209,'1961-01-22 00:00:00','Midway Island Naval Air Station','Military - U.S. Navy','Lockheed WV-2 Super Constellation',22,6,3,'While returning from an aborted barrier mission, the aircraft hit a seawall at end of short runway. The main landing geart was sheared off and the aircraft cartwheeled, slid into a vehicle, exploded and burned.','Midway Island Naval Air Station',22,1961,1,'winter',16),(2210,'1961-01-24 00:00:00','Mt. Burangrang, Indonesia','Garuda Indonesia Airlines','Douglas DC-3',21,21,0,'The aircraft struck Mt. Burangrang . Attempt by the pilot to fly over mountainous terrain when unsure of his position and in weather conditions which severely restricted visibility.','Mt. Burangrang, Indonesia',24,1961,1,'winter',0),(2211,'1961-01-26 00:00:00','Trinity Bay, Newfoundland','Military - U.S. Air Force','Douglas C-118A Liftmaster',23,23,0,'While approaching Argentia-Bristol Field, the  aircraft crashed into the Trinity Bay about 50 km northeast of Argentia. It is believed the aircraft disintegrated in the air possibly following a mechanical issue. However, due to a lack of evidence,  it was not possible to determine the exact cause of the accident.','Off Argentia, Azores',26,1961,1,'winter',0),(2212,'1961-01-28 00:00:00','Off Mont