ads in excess of the design loads. The aircraft entered an area of extreme turbulence and was struck by lightning.','Near Azul, Argentina',19,1961,7,'summer',0),(2233,'1961-07-21 00:00:00','Shemya, Alaska','Alaska Airlines','Douglas DC-6A',6,6,0,'Undershot the runway by 200 feet, crashed and burned. Absence of approach and runway lights. Lack of guidance from air traffic controller during last stages of flight.','Shemya, Alaska',21,1961,7,'summer',0),(2234,'1961-08-06 00:00:00','Budapest, Hungary','Malev Hungarian Airlines','Douglas DC-3',27,27,3,'The aircraft crashed between a row of houses while on a sightseeing flight. Inattention of crew to duties. Pilots had 2 companions in the cabin during the entire flight and performed forbidden maneuvers including one sharp turn which resulted in  lost control of the aircraft.','Budapest, Hungary',6,1961,8,'summer',0),(2235,'1961-08-09 00:00:00','Sola, Norway','Cunard Eagle Airways','Vickers Viking 3B',39,39,0,'Crashed into a mountain18 nm northeast of Stravanger Airport.  Deviation from prescribed course. Cause unknown.','Sola, Norway',9,1961,8,'summer',0),(2236,'1961-08-29 00:00:00','Sondreströmfjord, Greenland','Eastern Provincial Airways','de Havilland Canada DHC-3 Otter',6,1,0,'An in-flight fire, initiated and sustained by a severe fuel leak. The fuel leak was caused by the locking of a carburetor drain plug to unscrew.','Sondreströmfjord, Greenland',29,1961,8,'summer',5),(2237,'1961-09-01 00:00:00','Near Hinsdale, Illinois','Trans World Airlines','Lockheed 049 Constellation',78,78,0,'The aircraft crashed and burned in a field 10 miles west of Midway Airport. The airliner had taken off from Midway headed for Las Vegas. Loss of a 5/16 inch steel bolt from the elevator boost system which caused the elevator to move to its full upward position creating a stall and loss of control of the aircraft.','Near Hinsdale, Illinois',1,1961,9,'autumn',0),(2238,'1961-09-05 00:00:00','Near Sendafar, Ethiopia','Ethiopian Airlines','Dou