proach ban applied by his operations manual.','Jersey, Channel Islands, UK',14,1965,4,'spring',1),(2558,'1965-04-23 00:00:00','Near Seattle, Washington','Aaxico Airlines','Douglas DC-6A',5,5,0,'The cargo plane flew into Mt. Rainier at 10,200 ft.  The improper correlation of the aircraft position with respect to obstructing terrain while continuing the flight on a VFR flight plan in instrument weather conditions.','Near Seattle, Washington',23,1965,4,'spring',0),(2559,'1965-05-05 00:00:00','Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain\rCanary Islands','Iberia Airlines','Lockheed 1049G-55 Super Constellation',49,30,0,'The pilot, who saw the beginning of the runway clearly, but not the rest of it, decided to make a very low run after which he re-applied power for a go-around. After starting his go-around, the aircraft struck a tractor located 50 meters from the runway edge. Heavily damaged, the plane crashed on the western edge of the diversion canal of the Rodeo gorge. Decision not to divert to Las Palmas in view of the weather conditions.','Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain\nCanary Islands',5,1965,5,'spring',19),(2560,'1965-05-20 00:00:00','Cairo, Egypt','Pakistan International Airlines','Boeing B-720-040B',127,121,0,'The aircraft  crashed during its approach.The plane descended during the approach at triple the normal rate until the aircraft struck the ground. The aircraft exceeded the recommended descent rate during the final stages of landing for reasons unknown.','Cairo, Egypt',20,1965,5,'spring',6),(2562,'1965-06-15 00:00:00','Near Colombus, Georgia','Military - U.S. Army / Military - U.S. Army','Bell UH-1D / Bell UH1D (helicopters)',18,18,0,'Two helicopters flying in formation, crashed in mid-air at Benning military base. Ten aboard 8760 and 8 aboard 8840 killed.','Near Colombus, Georgia',15,1965,6,'summer',0),(2563,'1965-06-25 00:00:00','Near Santa Ana, California','Military - U.S. Air Force','Boeing C-135A',85,85,0,'Crashed shortly after taking off from El Toro Marine Corps