r with a Mirage jet photographing the TU-144, overreacted causing a compressor stall. The aircraft then went into a dive and broke apart after the aircraft\'s design capacity was exceeded.','Goussainville, France',3,1973,6,'summer',0),(3242,'1973-06-09 00:00:00','Rio de Janeiro, Brazil','Varig','Boeing 707-327C',4,2,0,'The cargo plane was making an instrument approach to Runway 14 with the speed brake lever at 45 degrees and inboard spoilers deactivated when it was noted that the spoiler switch cover was open. The captain or copilot then closed the spoiler switch cover and activated the inboard spoiler causing the aircraft to pitch down. The plane descended from a height of about 70 meters and struck approach lights.','Rio de Janeiro, Brazil',9,1973,6,'summer',2),(3243,'1973-06-20 00:00:00','Near Puerto Vallarta, Mexico','Aeromexico','McDonnell Douglas DC-9-15',27,27,0,'The aircraft hit high ground during an approach, 32 kms from the airport.','Near Puerto Vallarta, Mexico',20,1973,6,'summer',0),(3244,'1973-06-30 00:00:00','Amman, Jordan','Aeroflot','Tupolev TU-134A',85,2,7,'The aircraft was not able to lift off during takeoff, overshot the runway and crashed into a house bursting into flames.','Amman, Jordan',30,1973,6,'summer',83),(3245,'1973-07-04 00:00:00','Near Shakhtyorsk, Russia','Aeroflot','Ilyushin IL-14',18,18,0,'Controlled flight into terrain, 53 km south of Shakhtyorsk. The crew descended below a safe altitude during the approach.','Near Shakhtyorsk, Russia',4,1973,7,'summer',0),(3246,'1973-07-09 00:00:00','Nnear Kuybyshev, Russia','Aeroflot','Tupolev TU-124V',61,2,0,'Made a forced landing after experiencing engine failure. Complete destruction of turbine and due to a design and manufacturing defect.','Nnear Kuybyshev, Russia',9,1973,7,'summer',59),(3247,'1973-07-11 00:00:00','Paris, Orly Airport, France','Varig','Boeing B-707-345C',134,123,0,'Fire aboard the aircraft in the aft right toilet was reported and an emergency descent made. The plane was heavily damaged by fire before fire fighters could rescue passengers. Most fatalities were due to CO before rescuers could reach passengers. The fire started in the aft right toilet either from an electrical short or discarded cigarette.','Paris, Orly Airport, France',11,1973,7,'summer',11),(3248,'1973-07-22 00:00:00','Off Papeete, Tahiti','Pan American World Airways','Boeing B-707-321B',79,78,0,'The aircraft crashed 30 seconds after takeoff from Faaa Airport into the ocean. Cause unknown.  It is possible an instrument failure diverted the crews attention during a turn. The aircraft was named \"Clipper Winged Racer.\"','Off Papeete, Tahiti',22,1973,7,'summer',1),(3249,'1973-07-23 00:00:00','St. Louis, Missouri','Ozark Air Lines','Fairchild-Hiller FH-227B',44,38,0,'The aircraft crashed after attempting to land in thunderstorms with heavy rain and high winds. After passing the outer marker, the aircraft descended below the glide slope, entered an area of heavy rain, was struck by lightning and crashed into the ground short of the runway. The aircraft\'s encounter with a downdraft following the captain\'s decision to initiate and continue an instrument approach into a thunderstorm. Lack of a timely issuance of a severe weather warning by the National Weather Service.','St. Louis, Missouri',23,1973,7,'summer',6),(3250,'1973-07-24 00:00:00','Honolulu, HI','Air Hawaii','Volpar C45G',5,5,0,'The plane experienced engine faiure while taking off and crashed into the ocean. Fuel starvation. Rear auxillary tanks not serviced. Overloaded, improper center of gravity.','Honolulu, HI',24,1973,7,'summer',0),(3251,'1973-07-31 00:00:00','Logan Airport, Boston, Massachusetts','Delta Air Lines','McDonnell Douglas DC-9-31',89,89,0,'The flight crashed into a seawall during ILS approach in adverse weather conditions. The failure of the flightcrew to monitor altitude and to recognize passage of the aircraft through the approach decision height during an unstabilized precision approach conducted in rapidly changing meteorological conditions. Poor positioning of the aircraft for an approach by ATC. Questionable information presented by the flight director.','Logan Airport, Boston, Massachusetts',31,1973,7,'summer',0),(3252,'1973-08-13 00:00:00','Near La  Coruña, Spain','Aviaco Condor','Sud-Aviation Caravelle 10-R',85,85,1,'The aircraft experienced two missing landing attempts. On the third try, the crew tried to descent below minimum safe altitude to make visual contact with the ground. The right wing clipped trees and the aircraft crashed about 2 m from the runway. Attempting to land in meteorological conditions that were below minima.','Near La  Coruña, Spain',13,1973,8,'summer',0),(3253,'1973-08-15 00:00:00','Don Don, Haiti','Private','Norman BN-2A-6',10,10,0,'While flying too low, the plane struck a mountain shrouded in clouds and located in Dondon, 21 km south of the airport. Controlled flight into terrain..','Don Don, Haiti',15,1973,8,'summer',0),(3254,'1973-08-18 00:00:00','Baku, Azerbaijan, USSR','Aeroflot','Antonov AN-24V',64,56,0,'Crashed after after attemping a return to the airport for an emergency landing. Left engine failure.','Baku, Azerbaijan, USSR',18,1973,8,'summer',8),(3255,'1973-08-22 00:00:00','El Yopal, Colombia','AVIANCA','Douglas DC-3',17,16,0,'Struck a hill in heavy fog. Flying VFR in IFR conditions.','El Yopal, Colombia',22,1973,8,'summer',1),(3256,'1973-08-27 00:00:00','Bogota, Colombia','Aerocondor Colombia','Lockheed L-188A Electra',42,42,0,'Crashed into El Cable Mountain after taking off in fog. Crew failed to follow departure procedures.','Bogota, Colombia',27,1973,8,'summer',0),(3257,'1973-08-28 00:00:00','Near Huete, Spain','Military - U.S. Air Force','Lockheed C-141A',25,24,0,'The aircraft was cleared to 5,000 ft. but descended to 3,000 ft. The plane hit a ridge became airborne, rolled over and crashed inverted into a ravine. The flying crew failed to follow approach procedures and descended to an unsafe altitude following a misinterpretation of the ATC clearance. A lack of crew coordination, a wrong planned approach and crew fatigue.','Thirty-five miles west of Los Angeles, California',28,1973,8,'summer',1),(3258,'1973-08-28 00:00:00','Near Huete, Spain','Military - U.S. Air Force','Lockheed C-141A',25,24,0,'The aircraft was cleared to 5,000 ft. but descended to 3,000 ft. The plane hit a ridge became airborne, rolled over and crashed inverted into a ravine. The flying crew failed to follow approach procedures and descended to an unsafe altitude following a misinterpretation of the ATC clearance. A lack of crew coordination, a wrong planned approach and crew fatigue.','Near Huete, Spain',28,1973,8,'summer',1),(3259,'1973-08-28 00:00:00','Thirty-five miles west of Los Angeles, California','Trans World Airlines','Boeing B-707-331B',149,1,0,'The plane porpoised while descending to LAX. The aircraft was subjected to 2 minutes of peak acceleration forces of 2.4 g.  A combination of design tolerances in the aircraft\'s longitudinal control system which, under certain conditions, produced a critical relationship between control forces and aircraft response.','Thirty-five miles west of Los Angeles, California',28,1973,8,'summer',148),(3260,'1973-08-28 00:00:00','Thirty-five miles west of Los Angeles, California','Trans World Airlines','Boeing B-707-331B',149,1,0,'The plane porpoised while descending to LAX. The aircraft was subjected to 2 minutes of peak acceleration forces of 2.4 g.  A combination of design tolerances in the aircraft\'s longitudinal control system which, under certain conditions, produced a critical relationship between control forces and aircraft response.','Near Huete, Spain',28,1973,8,'summer',148),(3261,'1973-09-08 00:00:00','King Cove, Alaska','World Airways','McDonnell Douglas DC-8-63F',6,6,0,'Hit mountain at 3,500 ft., in level flight, 15.5 miles east of airport in fog. Improper IFR operation.  Descended below MSA in mountainous terrain. The captain\'s deviation from approved instrument approach procedures. As a result of the deviation the flight descended into an area of unreliable navigation signals and obstructing terrain.','King Cove, Alaska',8,1973,9,'autumn',0),(3262,'1973-09-11 00:00:00','Moganik, Yugoslavia','JAT Yugoslav Airlines','Aerospatiale Caravelle 6N',41,41,0,'The aircraft struck Moganik Mountain at 6,300 ft., while descending. Controlled flight into terrain.','Moganik, Yugoslavia',11,1973,9,'autumn',0),(3263,'1973-09-20 00:00:00','Natchitoches, Louisiana','Private Charter','Beechcraft E18S',6,6,0,'The plane crashed into a tree 200 yards past the end of the runway while taking off  from Natchitoches, Louisiana Municipal Airport. A witness to the crash reported that the plane never seemed to gain any altitude. It scraped the top of a pecan tree, catching a wing and crashed to the ground. Pilot failed to see/avoid objects, obstructions. Pilot had severe coronary artery disease. Ran 3 miles from motel to airport.  May have had a heart attack. Singer Jim Croce, 30, killed.  Also killed were accompanist Maurice Muehleisen, publicist Kenny Cortese, road manager Dennis Rast, comedian George Stevens and pilot Robert Elliot. Croce\'s company had just completed a performance before a crowd of 2,000 at Northwest State University.','Natchitoches, Louisiana',20,1973,9,'autumn',0),(3264,'1973-09-27 00:00:00','Rich Mountain, Arkansas','Texas International Airlines','Convair 600',11,11,0,'The aircraft flew100 miles off course and struck Black Fork Mountain, 600 feet below the summit of the peak, 91 miles North of Texarkana. Heavy thunderstorms were in the area at the time. The captain\'s attempt to operate the flight under VFR at night without using all the navigational aids and information available to him and his deviation from the pre-planned route without adequate positioning information.','Rich Mountain, Arkansas',27,1973,9,'autumn',0),(3265,'1973-09-30 00:00:00','Miritituba, Brazil','Aeronorte','Douglas DC-3A',9,9,0,'The cr