polev TU-134A',93,70,0,'The plane made a hard landing, crashed and burst into flames after a straight-in hard landing without leveling off.','Kuybyshev, Russia',20,1986,10,'autumn',23),(4128,'1986-10-22 00:00:00','Manhattan, New York','Private - WNBC','Enstrom F-28F',2,2,0,'The helicopter was contracted by NBC to make daily highway traffic observations in the New York City area. The pilot and passenger, Jane Dornacker, a NBC radio traffic reporter, were flying in a northerly direction along manhattan\'s west side at an altitude of about 75 feet. Witnesses observed the aircraft\'s main rotor blades stop, the aircraft descended rapidly, struck the top of a chain link fence at a river pier, crashed into the HudsonRiver and sank in 15 to 20 feet of water. Investigation revealed the sprag clutch was inadequately lubricated, had \'rolled over\' in the opposite direction of its design and the sprag assembly was damaged. Several sprags and both activating springs were broken and different size sprags were installed. An unauthorized, overhauled clutch had been installed in the aircraft. Dornacker had survived another helicopter crash earlier in the year.','Manhattan, New York',22,1986,10,'autumn',0),(4129,'1986-10-23 00:00:00','Near Peshawar, Pakistan','Pakistan International Airlines','Fokker F-27 Friendship 600',54,13,0,'Crashed short of the runway on approach, broke up and landed inverted. Crew error. The aircraft was allowed to descent below MDA. Crew did not properly monitor the altitude.','Near Peshawar, Pakistan',23,1986,10,'autumn',41),(4130,'1986-10-30 00:00:00','Near Managua, Nicaragua','Military - Nicaraguan Air Force','Mil Mi-17 (helicopter)',23,21,0,'Either mechanical failure, weather or ground fire from Contra rebels brought the helicopter down.','Near Managua, Nicaragua',30,1986,10,'autumn',2),(4131,'1986-11-02 00:00:00','Near Zahedan, Iran','Military - Iranian Air Force','Lockheed C-130',103,103,0,'Struck the side of a mountain near the Pakistani border. Crew