a after taking off from Hiva Ou and experiencing engine failure. The crew didn\'t recognize the failure and concentrated on the low oil pressure warning. The approach was abandoned at the very last moment it was decided to carry out an unprepared ditching. The crew\'s performance may have been impacted by alcohol consumption.','Off Nuka Hiva, French Polynesia',19,1991,4,'spring',11),(4507,'1991-05-09 00:00:00','Sulawesi, Indonesia','Merpati Nusantara Airlines','Fokker F-27 Friendship 600',13,13,0,'Crashed into Mt. Klabat in heavy fog while descending for a landing.','Sulawesi, Indonesia',9,1991,5,'spring',0),(4508,'1991-05-13 00:00:00','Grand Canyon, Airzona','Air Taxi - Air Grand Canyon Inc.','Cessna 207A',7,7,0,'The airplane crashed into a wooded area about 8 minutes after takeoff. Detonation (or pre-ignition) in the number 1 cylinder, which resulted in erosion (burning) of the number 1 piston and subsequent loss of engine power. A factor related to the accident was: the lack of suitable terrain for an emergency landing.','Grand Canyon, Airzona',13,1991,5,'spring',0),(4509,'1991-05-15 00:00:00','La Poyatta, Colombia','ADES Colombia','Douglas C-47B',14,13,0,'Eight minutes after takeoff the No. 2 engine failed.  The pilot turned back but crashed 1 mile short of the runway.  The passengers were told to throw out cargo after which unfortunately they all moved towards the tail leading to a loss of control.','La Poyatta, Colombia',15,1991,5,'spring',1),(4510,'1991-05-23 00:00:00','Leningrad, USSR','Aeroflot','Tupolev TU-154B-1',181,13,0,'Undershot the runway and broke in half after a hard landing. Crew error. A rapid rate of descent, leading to landing gear failure. The accident happened durining daylight in a rain shower.','Leningrad, USSR',23,1991,5,'spring',168),(4511,'1991-05-24 00:00:00','Bakhtaran, Iran','Metro Cargo','Ilyushin 76TD',10,4,0,'After three missed approaches the cargo plane ran out of fuel and crashed.','Bakhtaran, Iran',24,1991,5,'spring',6),(4512,'1991-05-26 00:00:00','Near Ban Nong Rong, Thailand','Lauda Air','Boeing B-767-3Z9ER',223,223,0,'Twelve minutes after takeoff the crew received a visual REV ISLN advisory warning which indicated that an additional system failure may cause deployment of the No. 1 engine thrust reverser. No action was taken since the manual indicated \"No Action Required\". Just before reaching FL 310 during a climb, there was an uncommanded deployment of the No. 1 engine thrust reverser. The aircraft stalled, went into a steep high speed dive, broke apart at 4,000 feet and crashed into the jungle 70 miles northwest of Bangkok. Failure of the reverse thrust isolation valve. Following the accident Boeing made modifications to the thrust reverser system. The aircraft was named Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart.','Near Ban Nong Rong, Thailand',26,1991,5,'spring',0),(4513,'1991-06-01 00:00:00','Off Matthewtown, Great Inagua','Agape Flight Inc.','GAF Nomad N24A',3,2,0,'The aircraft ditched 1.25 miles off Grada Zuma, following a reported engine failure.','Off Matthewtown, Great Inagua',1,1991,6,'summer',1),(4514,'1991-06-10 00:00:00','Luanda, Angola','Carib Air Transport','Lockheed L-382B Hercules',7,7,0,'Crashed on takeoff after the No. 1engine overspeeded and failed.','Luanda, Angola',10,1991,6,'summer',0),(4515,'1991-06-20 00:00:00','Near Malambo, Colombia','Aerosucre Colombia','Douglas DC-6BF',18,2,0,'Following several attempts to land the pilot decided to hold until weather conditions improved.  Contact was lost with the plane and it flew into the ground. Visibility was reduced by low lying fog.','Near Malambo, Colombia',20,1991,6,'summer',16),(4516,'1991-06-26 00:00:00','Gulf of Finland, Russia','AKF Polet','Antonov AN-24',10,10,0,'The cargo plane crashed into the Gulf of Finland shortly after taking off.','Gulf of Finland, Russia',26,1991,6,'summer',0),(4517,'1991-06-26 00:00:00','Gulf of Finland, Russia','AKF Polet','Antonov AN-24',10,10,0,'The cargo plane crashed into the Gulf of Finland shortly after taking off.','Near Sokotu, Nigeria',26,1991,6,'summer',0),(4518,'1991-06-26 00:00:00','Near Sokotu, Nigeria','Okada Air','BAC One-Eleven 402AP',53,4,0,'The plane diverted to Sokotu due to poor weather. After circling for an hour, unable to locate the air field, the aircraft ran out of fuel and had to make a forced landing. The landing gear was torn off and the plane broke up during the ground slide.','Gulf of Finland, Russia',26,1991,6,'summer',49),(4519,'1991-06-26 00:00:00','Near Sokotu, Nigeria','Okada Air','BAC One-Eleven 402AP',53,4,0,'The plane diverted to Sokotu due to poor weather. After circling for an hour, unable to locate the air field, the aircraft ran out of fuel and had to make a forced landing. The landing gear was torn off and the plane broke up during the ground slide.','Near Sokotu, Nigeria',26,1991,6,'summer',49),(4520,'1991-07-04 00:00:00','El Yopal, Colombia','Helicol Colombia','de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter 300',3,3,0,'While attempting to land the pilot continued VFR flight in IFR conditions and collided with a hill.','El Yopal, Colombia',4,1991,7,'summer',0),(4521,'1991-07-09 00:00:00','Bellavista Airport, Peru','Aerochasqui','CASA 212 Aviocar 200',15,15,0,'The aircraft was shot at by drunken police in an attempt to stop it for a search when mistaken for drug smuggling. As the plane ascended through 75 ft. bullets penetrated the forward fuselage killing the pilot and copilot.','Bellavista Airport, Peru',9,1991,7,'summer',0),(4522,'1991-07-10 00:00:00','Birmingham, Alabama','L\'Express Airlines','Beechcraft BE-99-C99',15,13,0,'While the aircraft was on approach, it entered an area of thunderstorms. The aircraft rolled left and pitched up as the aircraft approached level flight. The aircraft then stalled and started to descend. The descent couldn\'t be arrested and the aircraft crashed into a residential area, destroying two homes and two automobiles.  Decision by the pilot-in-command to continue instrument approach into thunder