 and he delayed his decision to reverse course until he was unable to avoid the weather.','Near Alliford Bay, British Columbia, Canada2',18,1996,8,'summer',0),(4928,'1996-08-19 00:00:00','Belgrade, Yugosalvia','Spair Air Transport','Ilyushin IL-76T',12,12,0,'After taking off from Belgrade, the plane experienced electrical problems and returned to the airport. After dumping fuel and circling for 3 hours, the plane crashed into a corn field 800m short of the runway.','Belgrade, Yugosalvia',19,1996,8,'summer',0),(4929,'1996-08-29 00:00:00','Near Longyearbyen, Norway','Vnokovo Airlines','Tupolev TU-154M',141,141,0,'The aircraft crashed 7 nm short of the runway into Operafjellet Mountain at an altitude of 2,900 ft. while attempting to land in poor weather. The crew did not use the usual approach which includes a turn over the ocean, but rather took a route that led through a narrow valley. Inadequate planning, unsatisfactory crew resource management and monitoring, not discontinuing the approach when procedural uncertainties existed and limited knowledge of the operating language and the actual airspace. The passengers were mainly Russian coal miners headed for a Russian mine on one of the Norwegian islands.','Near Longyearbyen, Norway',29,1996,8,'summer',0),(4930,'1996-09-25 00:00:00','Waddenzee, Netherlands','Dutch Dakota Association','Douglas DC-3C',32,32,0,'Shortly after takeoff from Texel, a connecting rod bearing in the No.1 engine failed. The prop was feathered.  Soon after, a part of the feathering mechanism failed and the prop started windmilling causing drag. The aircraft rapidly descended and crashed onto a mud-flat. The accident was initiated by a combined failure of the left engine and the left feathering system. The accident became inevitable when the flight crew allowed the speed to decrease below stall speed and lost control of the aircraft at an altitude from which recovery was not possible.','Waddenzee, Netherlands',25,1996,9,'autumn',0),(4931,'1996-10-02 00:00:00','Off Pasamayo, Peru','Aeroperu','Boeing B-757-200',70,70,0,'The aircraft crashed into the ocean 28 minutes after taking off from Lima, Peru. Pieces of adhesive tape were found covering the static ports, placed there by personnel during aircraft maintenance and cleaning, causing the malfunction of the airspeed indicators and altimeters. The crew was not able to correctly determine their altitude and airspeed and with no ground reference over water and at night, crashed into the sea. An employee did not remove the adhesive tape from the static ports, nor was it detected by any number of people, including the captain, during the preflight inspection. A maintenance worker was tried and convicted of negligent homicide for failing to remove the adhesive tape and received 2 years in jail.','Off Pasamayo, Peru',2,1996,10,'autumn',0),(4932,'1996-10-03 00:00:00','Kahemba, Congo','Malu Aviation','de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter 200',21,6,0,'Crashed on take off.','Kahemba, Congo',3,1996,10,'autumn',15),(4933,'1996-10-06 00:00:00','Lukapa, Angola','Savanair','Antonov 12B',19,6,0,'While attempting to land the landing lights malfunctioned causing the cargo plane to veer off the runway and crash into a house.','Lukapa, Angola',6,1996,10,'autumn',13),(4934,'1996-10-08 00:00:00','San Francesco al Campo, Italy','Aeroflot','Antonov An-124',23,2,2,'The cargo plane struck trees and a house while making a second attempt to land. Poor communication and lack of training for the crew. Poor planning approach, the decision to leave late in the second round. \rStructural deficiencies in engine control.','San Francesco al Campo, Italy',8,1996,10,'autumn',21),(4935,'1996-10-22 00:00:00','Manta, Ecuador','Million Air','Boeing B-707-323C',4,4,30,'The cargo plane, carrying flowers and frozen fish crashed into the Dolorosa district, bursting into flames shortly after taking off. One engine caught fire during the climb-out.','Manta, Ecuador',22,1996,10,'autumn',0),(4936,'1996-10-26 0