 control. Factors associated with the accident were pressure by the company to continue flights in marginal weather, and the \"flat\" lighting leading to whiteout conditions.','Coron, Philippines',9,1999,6,'summer',0),(5119,'1999-06-17 00:00:00','Goroka, Papua New Guinea','Airlink','Embraer 110P2 Bandeirante',17,17,0,'The aircraft was 19 miles or six minutes out of Goroka when it crashed into a hillside. At the time of the crash, the pilot was in routine communication with Goroka and gave no indications of any problems.','Goroka, Papua New Guinea',17,1999,6,'summer',0),(5120,'1999-06-25 00:00:00','Long Haul Lake, Manatoba, Canada','Blue Water Aviation Services','de Havilland Canada DHC-3 Otter',2,1,0,'During the takeoff the engine failed and the plane crashed into trees. The most likely accident scenario during the second take-off is that water contamination migrated from the center fuel tank to the engine,\rresulting in a loss of engine power.','Long Haul Lake, Manatoba, Canada',25,1999,6,'summer',1),(5121,'1999-07-01 00:00:00','Luzamba, Angola','Savanair','Antonov 12B',5,1,0,'The cargo plane was shot down by UNITA rebels.','Luzamba, Angola',1,1999,7,'summer',4),(5122,'1999-07-02 00:00:00','Sittwe, Myanmar','Myanmar Airways','Fokker F-27 Friendship 600',8,8,0,'The aircraft, carrying freight, flew into the side of a fog covered ridge, 8 km E of Sittwe, while on approach to Sittwe.','Sittwe, Myanmar',2,1999,7,'summer',0),(5123,'1999-07-04 00:00:00','Villavicencio, Colombia','LANC Colombia','Douglas DC-6A',18,5,0,'The aircraft developed engine trouble shortly after taking off and returned to the airport. The plane made a steep descent and struck an embankment of the Guatiquia River.','Villavicencio, Colombia',4,1999,7,'summer',13),(5124,'1999-07-07 00:00:00','Near Kathmandu, Nepal','Lufthansa Cargo Airlines','Boeing 727-243F',5,5,0,'The cargo plane crashed into the Champadevi mountains at an altitude of 7,500 ft. The plane was flying too low.  Failure to the adhere to