ternate destination, the flightcrew not following company and FAA procedures/directives, the lack of certification of the second pilot, the operator not following company and FAA procedures/directives, and the dark night and the low ceiling.','Nurnberg, Germany',8,2001,2,'winter',4),(5252,'2001-02-10 00:00:00','Jakobkondre, Suriname','Gum Air Charter','GAF Nomad N24A',10,10,0,'After losing radio contact with the airport, the aircraft was observed flying low before crashed into a mountainside 2 nm from Jakobkondre.','Jakobkondre, Suriname',10,2001,2,'winter',0),(5253,'2001-02-27 00:00:00','Near Granton Harbour, Scotland','Loganair','Shorts 360-100',2,2,0,'Double engine failure on take off cause the cargo plane to ditch in Firth of the Forth estuary. Icing.','Near Granton Harbour, Scotland',27,2001,2,'winter',0),(5254,'2001-03-03 00:00:00','Unadilla, Georgia','Military - Florida Army National Guard','Short 360',21,21,0,'The plane was on a flight from Florida to Oceana Naval Air Station in Virginia when witnesses observed the plane gliding down and losing altitude until it impacted the ground, exploding into flames. Heavy rain and wind were present in the area at the time of the accident. Weight imbalances in the aircraft were the primary cause of the accident as the cargo shifted when the pilot  got up and walked through the plane toward the rear of the plane, unbalancing the aircraft just as it hit severe turbulence. This led to the loss of control and break-up of the aircraft.','Unadilla, Georgia',3,2001,3,'spring',0),(5255,'2001-03-03 00:00:00','Unadilla, Georgia','Military - Florida Army National Guard','Short 360',21,21,0,'The plane was on a flight from Florida to Oceana Naval Air Station in Virginia when witnesses observed the plane gliding down and losing altitude until it impacted the ground, exploding into flames. Heavy rain and wind were present in the area at the time of the accident. Weight imbalances in the aircraft were the primary cause of the accident 