g the maximum limit of 180 knots stipulated throughout the procedure, and using a bank angle inferior to the recommended 25 to 30 degrees, thereby departing holding pattern obstacle protection, leading to a collision against the Cumbal Volcano.','Near Ipiales, Colombia',28,2002,1,'winter',0),(5334,'2002-02-12 00:00:00','Near Khorramabed, Iran','Iran Air Tours','Tupolev TU-154',117,117,0,'Crashed against the side of a mountain in heavy fog in the Sefid Kouh mountain range while on approach to Khorramabad. The plane was totally destroyed and scattered in small pieces across the mountain. Pilot error.','Near Khorramabed, Iran',12,2002,2,'winter',0),(5335,'2002-02-15 00:00:00','Monrovia, Liberia','Tiramavia','Antonov 12BP',10,1,0,'The cargo plane crashed while attempting to make an emergency landing.','Monrovia, Liberia',15,2002,2,'winter',9),(5336,'2002-02-21 00:00:00','Lakhta, Russia','Military - Russian Navy','Antonov AN-26',20,17,0,'The plane was making an emergency landing after two previous attempts in heavy snow and strong winds when it clipped treetops and crashed into a field, approximately 1.5km short of the runway.','Lakhta, Russia',21,2002,2,'winter',3),(5337,'2002-02-22 00:00:00','Off Dumaguete, Philippines','Military - U.S. Army','MH-47 Chinook helicopter',10,10,0,'A helicopter ferrying U.S. troops in a counter-terrorism exercise, crashed into the sea, 30 minutes before its scheduled arrival at Mactan Island. The helicopter was flying in tandem with another U.S. Army Chinook when it crashed.','Off Dumaguete, Philippines',22,2002,2,'winter',0),(5338,'2002-03-09 00:00:00','Monte Rotondo, Italy','Svedijos Prekés','Antonov 2TP',3,3,0,'While en route the cargo plane impacted the side of a mountain at an altitude of 6,167 ft.  Pilot error. The crew did not conform to the VFR that required a track change to maintain the required flight parameters and/or a diversion to a suitable alternate airport.','Monte Rotondo, Italy',9,2002,3,'spring',0),(5339,'2002-03-14 00: