ht, about 40 miles north-northwest of Talkeetna, Alaska. The airplane was being operated as a visual flight rules. The pilot\'s failure to maintain adequate airspeed which resulted in an inadvertent stall, an uncontrolled descent and in-flight collision with terrain. A factor associated with the accident was rising terrain','Talkeetna, Alaska',28,2003,5,'spring',0),(5409,'2003-06-01 00:00:00','Milan, Italy','Eurojet Italila','Gates Learjet 45',2,2,0,'Shortly after taking off the jet nosed into the ground. Malfunction of the trim tab system.','Milan, Italy',1,2003,6,'summer',0),(5410,'2003-06-04 00:00:00','Near Oiapoque,  Brazil','Air Taxi - Marco Zero Air Taxi','EMB 721C Sertanejo',5,5,0,'Forty miles into it flight the aircraft crashed into the Amazon forest. The aircraft was not certified for IFR flight. Heavy cloud cover existed along the flight route.','Near Oiapoque,  Brazil',4,2003,6,'summer',0),(5411,'2003-06-06 00:00:00','Christchurch, New Zealand','Charter - Air Adventures New Zealand Ltd','Piper PA-31-350 Navajo Chieftain',10,8,0,'The aircraft crashed short of the runway in fog while on approach to Christchurch Airport. The plane crashed two kilometers from the airport, hitting a farm hedge and sliding across a paddock before smashing into a row of trees.','Christchurch, New Zealand',6,2003,6,'summer',2),(5412,'2003-06-11 00:00:00','Belo Horizonte, Brazil','Astro Air Taxi','Embraer 820C Navajo',4,4,0,'After takeoff, the pilot reported low pressure of oil  in an engine and  decided to return to the airport. The plane made a 270 degree turn in the final approach, stalled  and crashed to the ground.','Belo Horizonte, Brazil',11,2003,6,'summer',0),(5413,'2003-06-15 00:00:00','Volcano, Hawaii','Paradise Tour Helicopters','McDonnell Douglas 369D',4,4,0,'The helicopter impacted a lava field on the Pulama Pali in the Volcanoes National Park, Volcano, Hawaii.  A loss of engine power due to the fatigue fracture and separation of the compressor coupling adapter. The fatigue fracture was initiated by fretting on the pilot diameter due to both the inadequate design of the coupling and the coaxial misalignment of the spur adapter gear, compressor-coupling adapter, and compressor impeller during recent engine maintenance where the gearbox was removed and replaced. A factor in the accident was the unsuitable nature of the terrain to make an emergency landing.','Volcano, Hawaii',15,2003,6,'summer',0),(5414,'2003-06-22 00:00:00','Near Brest, France','Brit Air','Canadair CRJ-100ER',24,1,0,'The aircraft crashed onto a road and caught fire 1 km from Brest-Guipavas Airport in France\'s Brittany region, killing the pilot and injuring three others. There were thunderstorms in the area with 800 meters visibility at the time the accident took place.','Near Brest, France',22,2003,6,'summer',23),(5415,'2003-06-25 00:00:00','Near Rudshour, Iran','Military - Islamic Republic of Iran Air Force','Lockheed C-130 Hercules',7,7,0,'Nose dived into the ground shortly after takeoff near the Shur River.','Anchor Point, Alaska',25,2003,6,'summer',0),(5416,'2003-06-25 00:00:00','Near Rudshour, Iran','Military - Islamic Republic of Iran Air Force','Lockheed C-130 Hercules',7,7,0,'Nose dived into the ground shortly after takeoff near the Shur River.','Near Rudshour, Iran',25,2003,6,'summer',0),(5417,'2003-06-25 00:00:00','Anchor Point, Alaska','Hallo Bay Air - Air Taxi','Cessna 180H',3,3,0,'The airlpane is presumed to have collided with the ocean waters of the Cook Inlet, about 7 miles southwest of Anchor Point, Alaska. No wreckage has been located, and the airplane is presumed to be destroyed. A fatally injured passenger was located on July 3, in ocean waters near Anchor Point. An in-flight collision with water for an undetermined reason.','Anchor Point, Alaska',25,2003,6,'summer',0),(5418,'2003-06-25 00:00:00','Anchor Point, Alaska','Hallo Bay Air - Air Taxi','Cessna 180H',3,3,0,'The airlpane is presumed to have collided with the ocean waters of the Cook Inlet, about 7 miles southwest of Anchor Point, Alaska. No wreckage has been located, and the airplane is presumed to be destroyed. A fatally injured passenger was located on July 3, in ocean waters near Anchor Point. An in-flight collision with water for an undetermined reason.','Near Rudshour, Iran',25,2003,6,'summer',0),(5419,'2003-06-26 00:00:00','Near Rooisand Desert Ranch, Namibia','Comvac Aviation','Cessna 208B Grand Caravan',4,4,0,'Shortly after taking off the air ambulance hit a hill side in the Gamsberg Mountains.','Near Rooisand Desert Ranch, Namibia',26,2003,6,'summer',0),(5420,'2003-06-30 00:00:00','Blida, Algeria','Military - Algerian Air Force','Lockheed C-130H Hercules',4,4,11,'The military plane crashed into houses in the Beni Mered neighborhood, west of the Algerian capital, shortly after takeoff from the Boufarik military airport, 25 miles southwest of the capital. Witnesses reported seeing an engine on fire prior to the crash.','Blida, Algeria',30,2003,6,'summer',0),(5421,'2003-07-01 00:00:00','Belem, Para, Brazil','Heringer Air Taxi','Mitsubishi MU 2B 35',4,4,0,'The plane crashed on final approach to Belem Airport during a strong  thunderstorm.','Belem, Para, Brazil',1,2003,7,'summer',0),(5422,'2003-07-05 00:00:00','Macaé, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil','BHS - Brazilian Helicopter Services','Sikorsky  S 76 A',5,5,0,'The helicopter  was landing on the helideck of the ship Toisa Mariner, when the tail rotor collided with the flagpole on the ship. The pilot lost the control and the helicopter crashed into the  sea.','Macaé, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil',5,2003,7,'summer',0),(5423,'2003-07-08 00:00:00','Port Sudan, Sudan','Sudan Airways','Boeing 737-2J8C',117,117,0,'The plane\'s crew reported technical difficulties (engine failure) 10 minutes after taking off from Port Sudan Airport. The plane crashed into a hillside, 3 miles from the airport as the crew tried to return and make emergency landing. A three-year-old boy was the only survivor.','Port Sudan, Sudan',8,2