uinea',16,2008,4,'spring',0),(5679,'2008-04-28 00:00:00','Off Crimea, Black Sea','Naftogaz','Mil Mi-8T',20,20,0,'The helicopter crashed after the tail section hit the tower of the offshore drilling platform while it was attempting to land. The pilot was a trainee flying with an instructor. One survivor succumbed to his injuries soon after the crash.','Off Crimea, Black Sea',28,2008,4,'spring',0),(5680,'2008-05-17 00:00:00','Stehekin, Washington','Chelan Air Service','de Havilland Canada DHC-2 Mark I Beaver',5,2,0,'The float plane flipped and crashed as it attempted to land in Lake Chelan near Stehekin Lodge. It appeared the plane\'s wheels were deployed even though it was landing on water. The pilot\'s failure to retract the landing gear wheels prior to performing a water landing. Contributing to the accident were the pilot\'s disabling of the landing gear warning/advisory system and possible fatigue due to his work schedule.','Stehekin, Washington',17,2008,5,'spring',3),(5681,'2008-05-24 00:00:00','Two Harbors, Catalina Island, California','Island Express Helicopter Service','Eurocopter AS350D Astar',6,4,0,'The tour helicopter crashed near Banning House lodge in rain and poor visibility. The engine appears to have failed. Loss of engine power during approach for landing due to a fatigue fracture of a power turbine blade.','Two Harbors, Catalina Island, California',24,2008,5,'spring',2),(5682,'2008-05-26 00:00:00','Near Chelyabinsk, Russia','Moskovia Airlines','Antonov An-12',9,9,0,'The crew of the cargo plane reported a fire shortly after taking off from Chelyabinsk. The plane crashed in a field while attempting to make an emergency landing, after striking a power transmission line.','Near Chelyabinsk, Russia',26,2008,5,'spring',0),(5683,'2008-05-29 00:00:00','Panama City, Panama','Military - Servicio Aereo Nacional','Bell UN-1N Huey',12,11,0,'Chile\'s national police chief General Jose Alejandro Bernales, 59, and five others were killed when their helicopter crashed into a three story building. The helicopter pitched wildly before crashing into the building.','Panama City, Panama',29,2008,5,'spring',1),(5684,'2008-05-30 00:00:00','Tegucigalpa, Honduras','TACA International Airlines','Airbus A-320-233',136,3,2,'After making a missed approach and during the second attempt at landing at Toncontin Airport, the plane overran the runway, skidded across a street, struck cars and came to rest against an embankment. The runway was wet with rain from Tropical Storm Alma.','Tegucigalpa, Honduras',30,2008,5,'spring',133),(5685,'2008-06-08 00:00:00','Huntsville, Texas','PHI Air Medical','Bell 407',4,4,0,'The medical helicopter crashed into the Sam Houston National Forest while transporting a patient to a Houston hospital. The pilot\'s failure to identify and arrest the helicopter\'s descent, which resulted in its impact with terrain. Contributing to the accident was the pilot\'s inadvertent flight into instrument meteorological conditions, and the limited outside visual reference due to the dark night conditions, low clouds, and fog.','Huntsville, Texas',8,2008,6,'summer',0),(5686,'2008-06-10 00:00:00','Khartoum, Sudan','Sudan Airways','Airbus A-310-324',214,32,0,'While landing in poor weather, the plane skidded off the runway, hit navigation poles and burst into flames. The plane had flown from Amman via Damascus but been turned back once from Khartoum and forced to land in Port Sudan, on the Red Sea, because of bad weather, before being allowed to return to Khartoum. The accident was due to a long flaring distance (900 meters from R/W threshold) on a wet slippery runway without selecting Auto brake and with one deactivated engine reverse in such rainy conditions. The remaining available landing distance turned out to be too short to allow the captain to stop the aircraft before the end of the runway.','Khartoum, Sudan',10,2008,6,'summer',182),(5687,'2008-06-18 00:00:00','Hyannis, Massachusetts','Wiggins Airways','de Havilland Canada DHC-6 Twin Otter 100',1,1,0,'The cargo plane took off, reached about 200 feet, rolled over to the right and impacted the ground, nose first. The pilot\'s failure to remove the flight control lock prior to takeoff. Contributing to the accident was the FAA\'s failure to issue an airworthiness directive making the manufacturer\'s previously issued flight control lock service bulletins mandatory.','Hyannis, Massachusetts',18,2008,6,'summer',0),(5688,'2008-06-20 00:00:00','Bannang Sata, Thailand','Military - Thai Army','Bell UH-1N',10,10,0,'The military helicopter developed a mechanical problem and crashed into a hill while attemping to land.','Bannang Sata, Thailand',20,2008,6,'summer',0),(5689,'2008-06-26 00:00:00','Near Salak Mountain, Indonesia','Military - Indonesian Air Force','CASA NC-212',18,18,0,'The plane went missing in an area approximately 60 miles south of Jakarta while on a aerial surveillance mission.','Near Salak Mountain, Indonesia',26,2008,6,'summer',0),(5690,'2008-06-27 00:00:00','Near Malakal, Sudan','Juba Air Cargo','Antonov 12BK',8,7,0,'The cargo plane crashed mid-flight after entering an area of thunderstorms. Triple engine failure.','Near Malakal, Sudan',27,2008,6,'summer',1),(5691,'2008-06-29 00:00:00','Flagstaff, Arizona','Air Methods / Classic Helicopters','Bell 407 / Bell 407',7,6,0,'The two helicopters struck each other in mid-air and crashed in a wooded area about 0.5 miles from Flagstaff Medical Center. Both helicopter pilots\' failure to see and avoid the other helicopter on approach to the helipad. Contributing to the accident were the failure of N407GA\'s pilot to follow arrival and noise abatement guidelines and the failure of N407MJ\'s pilot to follow communications guidelines.','Flagstaff, Arizona',29,2008,6,'summer',1),(5692,'2008-06-30 00:00:00','Near Khartoum, Sudan','Ababeel Aviaition','Ilysushin Il-76TD',4,4,0,'While taking off, the cargo plane hit an electricity pole, crashed into a field and burst into flames. All four crew members were killed.','Near Khartoum, Sudan',30,2008,6,'summer',0),(5693,'2008-07-06 00:00:00','Saltillo, Mexico','USA Jet Airlines','Douglas DC9-15F',2,1,0,'While attempting to land, the cargo plane, loaded with auto parts, and experiencing engine trouble, crashed splitting into four pieces and scattering debris across an area of about 600 meters in diameter. The pilot was killed and the copilot seriously injured.','Saltillo, Mexico',6,2008,7,'summer',1),(5694,'2008-07-07 00:00:00','Near Bogota, Colombia','Centurian Air Cargo','Boeing B-747-209BSF',8,0,3,'The cargo plane carrying a load of flowers had taken off from Bogota when the crew radioed that they had an engine fire. They attempted to return to the airport, but crashed in a field and destroyed a farm house killing three people inside. Double engine failure.','Near Bogota, Colombia',7,2008,7,'summer',8),(5695,'2008-07-31 00:00:00','Owatonna, Minnesota','East Coast Jets','British Aerospace BAe-125-800A',8,8,0,'While attempting to land on Runway 30, the business jet landed 500 to 1000 feet down a 5,000 ft. runway, overran the runway, passed over a ditch and roadway, slid into a cornfield and broke up. One person survived the accident but died later. The pilots  were both working on insufficient sleep and displayed poor coordination with one another. The pilots failed to account for a wet runway and 8-knot tailwind when they touched down on the 5,500-foot runway, and they should have applied a braking system a full seven seconds earlier than they did.Realizing they were running out of runway, the pilots hit the throttles to try to take off again. Had the pilots hit the lift dump right after touchdown, or landed into the wind, the plane probably could have stopped safely on the runway. The accident was due to the captain\'s decision to attempt a go-around late in the landing roll with insufficient runway remaining. Contributing to the accident were the pilots\' poor crew coordination and lack of cockpit discipline.; 